cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD 

The paper is primarily focused on information retrieval (IR) tasks such as event detection, ad-hoc search, timeline generation, and real-time summarization over Arabic tweets. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as query expansion and crowd-worker annotations, which are relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of multiple subsets of the collection for better availability, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves the use of manual annotations and filtering techniques, which are relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
